    div.container.marketing
      h2.text-center Core features
      p.lead A restful json API, data models and a few helpful utilities
      div.row
        div.col-sm-4
          h3
            i.fa.fa-hand-o-right
            |  Signup
          p.
            The <code>/signup</code> endpoint makes sure the supplied username
            and email address are unique and creates new <code>User</code> and
            <code>Account</code> documents.
        div.col-sm-4
          h3
            i.fa.fa-sign-in
            |  Login
          p.
            When supplied valid credentials, the <code>/login</code> endpoint
            creates a new <code>Session</code>.  We've also included
            endpoints for resetting a forgotten password.
        div.col-sm-4
          h3
            i.fa.fa-paper-plane
            |  Email utility
          p.
            The <code>/contact</code> endpoint demonstrates the built-in email
            utility. By composing Handlebars and Markdown, personalized emails
            with HTML and text parts share one template.
      div.row
        div.col-sm-4
          h3
            i.fa.fa-user
            |  Users and roles
          p.
            <code>User</code> documents store login credentials and roles.
            Aqua ships with two roles; <code>Account</code> and
            <code>Admin</code>.
        div.col-sm-4
          h3
            i.fa.fa-users
            |  Admin groups
          p.
            Aqua also ships with an <code>Admin</code> grouping facility
            (<code>AdminGroup</code>). Think about these like departments;
            sales, support, manager, etc...
        div.col-sm-4
          h3
            i.fa.fa-key
            |  Permissions
          p.
            Permissions can be granted to an <code>AdminGroup</code> or
            individually for an <code>Admin</code>. <code>Admin</code>
            permissions will win over their group's permission.
